#: ../../../contributing/index.md:1
msgid "Contributing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/index.md:14
msgid ""
"Welcome! Happy to see you willing to make the project better. Have you read "
"the entire [user documentation](https://black.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) yet?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/index.md:17
msgid "Bird's eye view"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/index.md:21
msgid ""
"In terms of inspiration, _Black_ is about as configurable as _gofmt_ (which "
"is to say, not very). This is deliberate. _Black_ aims to provide a "
"consistent style and take away opportunities for arguing about style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/index.md:25
msgid ""
"Bug reports and fixes are always welcome! Please follow the [issue templates "
"on GitHub](https://github.com/psf/black/issues/new/choose) for best results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/index.md:29
msgid ""
"Before you suggest a new feature or configuration knob, ask yourself why you "
"want it. If it enables better integration with some workflow, fixes an "
"inconsistency, speeds things up, and so on - go for it! On the other hand, "
"if your answer is \"because I don't like a particular formatting\" then "
"you're not ready to embrace _Black_ yet. Such changes are unlikely to get "
"accepted. You can still try but prepare to be disappointed."
msgstr ""

